KnowledgeBase.Title: Example Dictionary compareLE 004
KnowledgeBase.RelatedFunctions: compare compareEQ compareNE compareGE compareLT compareGT

Example.Description: These examples use the compareLE function to compare two Dictionaries and return the Boolean value, true or false. The corresponding keys and values of each Dictionary are compared to determine whether one Dictionary is lesser than or equal to the other.

Syntax.Note: The first Dictionary is lesser than the second Dictionary.
